Mission.Briefing:
////////////BRIEFING////////////
Following the successful completion of Phase 1 of the BLUFOR plan of attack, BLUFOR is now commencing Phase 2. REDFOR is currently reeling due to the loss of several key Russian airfields, most notably their main fighter/logistics hub of Maykop. Phase 2 involves a strong push to the southeast, with the end goal of capturing the enemy occupied Sukhumi airport, as well as several larger strategic strike objectives.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- DETAILED BRIEFING -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
THIS MISSION RELIES ON PLAYERS UTILIZING THE F10 MENU AS FOLLOWS:
"Get Current Missions" -> Get Current Targets in Theater. Eliminating these targets will create opportunities that can be exploited on the Russian front-line.
"Deploy Airport Security Forces" -> Send a C-130 to capture an airfield. Make sure you've cleared out the area of hostiles, and protect it on it's way in. When it arrives it will deploy Anti air assets to hold the territory.
"Deploy FARP/WAREHOUSE Security Forces" -> Send a Blackhawk to one of the FARPs near the center of the theater. If there are no players running transport helos this will be needed to capture the FARPS which will resupply your airfields. Ensure the area around the FARP is clear of hostiles and escort the chopper to ensure he arrives.
CTLD is enabled and will need to be used to ensure your airbases are resupplied. Transport helos must deploy troops to the FARPS listed in the briefing and the F10 menu option "Get Warehouse Status". At least one of these FARPs must be under blue control to resupply blue airbases.

What is Georgia At War?
Georgia At War is an online, PVE dynamic campaign, where players start with a small foothold in Russian territory near Ukraine and must fight to increase their territory/bases and roll REDFOR back. The campaign is broken into two phases, each of which is a unique MP mission (hosted on the Hoggit Dedicated Server). Phase one starts with BLUFOR operating out of Anapa and making a large push to capture the airbase at Maykop to push REDFOR south and expand BLUFOR's area of operations. Once Maykop has been cleared and is under BLUFOR control, Phase two kicks off and BLUFOR switches gears and pushes for Sukhumi Airport (as well as several larger strategic objectives). Players must clear and capture territory to create forward bases to keep the pressure up on the enemy and to keep their airfields supplied. You are pitted against an AI commander who will react to your actions, he'll counter-attack territory you've captured, capture territory you aren't guarding, and in general do his best to foil your efforts to extend your front line southeast.
